direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods generate ID numbers but with different validity outcomes.
Both methods construct parts of the ID number with similar control flows and data handling.
The generateInvalid method relies on the checksum method for generating the invalid ID number.
The generateInvalid method uses the randomGender method to determine the gender for the ID number.
The generateInvalid method indirectly relies on the birthday method through the basePart method.
